io.iron.ironmq

Class Queue

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.iron.ironmq.Queue

  • public class Queue
extends java.lang.Object
    The Queue class represents a specific IronMQ queue bound to a client.

      • get

        public Message get()
            throws java.io.IOException
        Retrieves a Message from the queue. If there are no items on the queue, an EmptyQueueException is thrown.
        Throws:
        EmptyQueueException - If the queue is empty.
        HTTPException - If the IronMQ service returns a status other than 200 OK.
        java.io.IOException - If there is an error accessing the IronMQ server.

      • get

        public Messages get(int numberOfMessages)
             throws java.io.IOException
        Retrieves Messages from the queue. If there are no items on the queue, an EmptyQueueException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        numberOfMessages - The number of messages to receive. Max. is 100.
        Throws:
        EmptyQueueException - If the queue is empty.
        HTTPException - If the IronMQ service returns a status other than 200 OK.
        java.io.IOException - If there is an error accessing the IronMQ server.

      • peek

        public Message peek()
             throws java.io.IOException
        Peeking at a queue returns the next messages on the queue, but it does not reserve them. If there are no items on the queue, an EmptyQueueException is thrown.
        Throws:
        EmptyQueueException - If the queue is empty.
        HTTPException - If the IronMQ service returns a status other than 200 OK.
        java.io.IOException - If there is an error accessing the IronMQ server.
